<subsection xml:id="subsec-volume-of-a-cone">
    <title>Volume of a Cone</title>
        <activity>
            <statement>
                <p>
                  Constructing a cone.  
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Materials Needed 
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                 Sheets of paper or cardboard
                            </p><p>
                                 Scissors, glue/tape, and rulers
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                A cylinder (e.g., cup or bottle) for comparison
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                             "How can we turn this into a cone?"
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            Take a piece of paper and <m>\textbf{cut a circle}</m> any radius.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            <m>\textbf{Cut out a sector and roll}</m> the remaining part into a cone shape.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                           Measure the radius and height of their cones. 
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                           Calculate the volume using the formula .
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <ul marker="square">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Equally, we can try this activity using; Empty Ice cream cones,  A cylindrical cup of the <m>\textbf{same height}</m> and <m>\textbf{base}</m> as the cone and water.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                           ðŸ”¹ Steps: 
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Fill the cone with water and pour it into the cylinder severally until the cylinder is full.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            How many cones of rice will fill the cylinder?
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                           <m>\textbf{Notice that it takes exactly 3 full cones to fill the cylinder}</m>.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            This is why the formula includes <m>\frac{\textbf{1}}{\textbf{3}} </m>!
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            ðŸ”¹ Mathematical Insight</p>
                                           <p>
                                            âœ” This shows the formula:
                                           </p> <p><me> V_\text{cone} = \frac{1}{3} V_\text{cylinder} = \frac{1}{3} \pi r^2h</me>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>âœ” The cone is one-third of the volume of a cylinder with the same base and height.
                                            
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                        </li>  
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
        </activity>   
        <example>
            <statement>
               <sidebyside>
                 <p>
                    Find the volume of the following cone (correct to 1 decimal place):
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
               <latex-image label="cone-volume">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                     % Draw the entire cone with one uniform color
                    \fill[blue!40] (-2,0) arc (180:360:2 and 0.7) -- (2,0) arc (0:180:2 and 0.7) -- cycle;
                    \fill[blue!40] (-2,0) -- (0,4) -- (2,0) -- cycle;
                    
                    % Draw the base ellipse
                    \draw[thick] (-2,0) arc (180:360:2 and 0.7);
                    \draw[dashed] (2,0) arc (0:180:2 and 0.7);
                    
                    % Draw the cone's sides
                    \draw[thick] (-2,0) -- (0,4);
                    \draw[thick] (2,0) -- (0,4);
                    
                    % Draw the height
                    \draw[dashed] (0,0) -- (0,4);
                    \node[left] at (0.4,2) {28cm};
                    
                    % Draw the radius
                    \draw[dashed] (0,0) -- (2,0);
                    \node[below] at (1,0) {14 cm};
                \end{tikzpicture}
               </latex-image>
               </image>
               </sidebyside> 
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                   Step 1: Find the area of the base .
                   <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Area of a Circle} = \amp \pi r^2 </mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp \frac{22}{7} \times 14\, \text{cm} \times 14 \, \text{cm} </mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp 616{cm}^2 </mrow>
                   </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Step 2: Calculate the volume
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{V} =\amp \frac{1}{3} \times \pi r^2\times H </mrow>
                        <mrow> = \amp 616\, \text{cm}^2 \times 28\,  \text{cm} </mrow>
                        <mrow>  = 17, 248\, \text{cm}^3 \amp </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example> 
